<CSSOffset>
<summary>
The <strong><c>offset</c></strong> CSS <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Shorthand_properties">shorthand property</see> sets all the properties required for animating an element along a defined path. The offset properties together help to define an <strong>offset transform</strong>, a <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_transforms/Using_CSS_transforms">transform</see> that aligns a point in an element (<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/offset-anchor">offset-anchor</see>) to an <strong>offset position</strong> (<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/offset-position">offset-position</see>) on a path (<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/offset-path">offset-path</see>) at various points along the path (<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/offset-distance">offset-distance</see>) and optionally rotates the element (<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/offset-rotate">offset-rotate</see>) to follow the direction of the path.
</summary>
<remarks>
